habitat_description:
From SWReGAP
Occurs in a wide variety of habitats including shortgrass prairie, sandhills, shrubby hillsides, canyons, open stands of ponderosa pine in the foothills, pinon-juniper woodlands, arid river valleys. Habitats: coniferous and tropical hardwood forest, broadleaf woodland, river bottoms, rocky hillsides, prairies, sand dunes, farmland, suburban areas.

From NatureServe:
Palustrine Habitat(s): FORESTED WETLAND, Riparian, SCRUB-SHRUB WETLAND
Terrestrial Habitat(s): Bare rock/talus/scree, Cliff, Cropland/hedgerow, Desert, Forest - Conifer, Forest - Hardwood, Forest - Mixed, Grassland/herbaceous, Old field, Sand/dune, Savanna, Shrubland/chaparral, Suburban/orchard, Woodland - Conifer, Woodland - Hardwood, Woodland - Mixed

Habitat Comments: Habitats vary greatly among different geographic regions: semiarid to wet, lowland valleys to mountains, grasslands and shrublands to forests and forest edges, primary forest to secondary forest, sand dunes to rocky areas, and wilderness to semiagricultural and suburban (Campbell 1998, Lee 2000, Savage 2002, Ernst and Ernst 2003, Stebbins 2003).
